  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Multiple studies highlighted in the introduction have shown GeoGebra's positive impact on students' understanding, performance, and motivation when used in geometry instruction (Jia Yi Boo, 2016; Puotier Zutaah et al., 2023; Millicent Narh-Kert & Rufai Sabtiwu, 2022; Bhagat & Chang, 2015).",
    "A sizable portion of the existing research has focused specifically on using GeoGebra and related software for geometry teaching and learning.",
    "Early studies found GeoGebra had a significant effect on enhancing students' comprehension of the Van Hiele geometry model (Kutluca, 2013).",
    "Around the same time, Shadaan and Leong (2013) explored how primary students were able to interactively experiment with circles and spheres using GeoGebra, which resulted in improved learning outcomes compared to conventional methods.",
    "More recently, Jelatu and Ganesha (2018) demonstrated improved conceptual understanding of geometry topics across high school when GeoGebra was integrated into the broader mathematics curriculum."
  ],
